data.description:
Odaily Planet Daily News Kaito AI founder Yu Hu posted on the X platform that based on community feedback, the loyalty booster mechanism will be adjusted, pre-TGE and post-TGE projects will be considered separately, and general rankings (such as CT rankings) will not be included. This adjustment is to match the different reward mechanisms and maturity of the two types of projects. There are four reasons to retain the loyalty booster:
First, to create a fair competition environment and prevent large accounts from monopolizing the rankings;
Second, to encourage users to participate and pay attention for a long time;
Third, to highlight community members who focus on publishing content for a few projects;
Fourth, most project teams want to keep it, and the mechanism is customizable, and projects can be turned on and off as needed. At the same time, a newly upgraded Kaito Connect mechanism is being developed, which allows users to choose to associate with a few projects to increase their attention in these projects.
